referring to : https://github.com/aspnet/Razor/blob/dev/src/Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.Razor/DefaultTagHelperDescriptorFactory.cs#L387

Found this by inspection while working on similar code in Blazor. When walking up the inheritance chain, we use a dictionary to track property shadowing, but we also ignore any properties that don't meet our conditions - **without** creating an entry in the dictionary. 

This means the following wouldn't work but seems like it should.

```
public class A : ITagHelper
{
    public string Foo { get; set; }
}

public class B : A
{
    [HtmlAttributeNotBound] // Prevent callers from setting this, I will compute the value and set it
    public new string Foo { get; set; }
}
```
